Definition
The position property specifies how an element
is positioned in a webpage.

Types of Position
1. static  (Default)
2. relative
3. absolute
4. fixed
5. Sticky





position: static (Default)
Definition
-> Static is the default position.
->Elements follow normal document flow.
->Top, left, right, bottom do NOT work.
Example
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<style>
.box {
 position: static;
 background: lightblue;
 top: 50px; /* This will NOT work */
}
</style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="box">Static Box</div>

</body>
</html>

📌 It behaves normally. No movement.

